alidationReport\"}],\":\"]}]\n42:[\"$\",\"pre\",\"pre-3\",{\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L74\",\"code-0\",{\"language\":\"ts\",\"children\":\"export interface ValidationReport {\\n  violations: Violation[];\\n  slopScore: number;   // weighted total\\n  clean: boolean;\\n}\"}]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"43:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-19\",{\"children\":[\"Slop score is weighted: a \",[\"$\",\"code\",\"code-0\",{\"className\":\"$undefined\",\"node\":{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"code\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"banned-structure\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":145,\"column\":27,\"offset\":9034},\"end\":{\"line\":145,\"column\":45,\"offset\":9052}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":145,\"column\":27,\"offset\":9034},\"end\":{\"line\":145,\"column\":45,\"offset\":9052}}},\"children\":\"banned-structure\"}],\" hit counts triple a \",[\"$\",\"code\",\"code-1\",{\"className\":\"$undefined\",\"node\":{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"code\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"banned-word\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":145,\"column\":66,\"offset\":9073},\"end\":{\"line\":145,\"column\":79,\"offset\":9086}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":145,\"column\":66,\"offset\":9073},\"end\":{\"line\":145,\"column\":79,\"offset\":9086}}},\"children\":\"banned-word\"}],\" hit because structural tells are harder to miss as a reader. Word-level slips are forgivable; bold-colon prefixes are not.\"]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"44:[\"$\",\"h2\",\"h2-5\",{\"id\":\"how-do-you-repair-a-bad-ai-draft-without-making-it-worse\",\"className\":\"scroll-mt-24\",\"node\":{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"h2\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"How do you repair a bad AI draft without making it worse?\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":147,\"column\":4,\"offset\":9214},\"end\":{\"line\":147,\"column\":61,\"offset\":9271}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":147,\"column\":1,\"offset\":9211},\"end\":{\"line\":147,\"column\":61,\"offset\":9271}}},\"children\":\"How do you repair a bad AI draft without making it worse?\"}]\n45:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-20\",{\"children\":\"The naive answer is to retry until clean. That naive answer is wrong.\"}]\n46:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-21\",{\"children\":\"LLMs regress to the mean on every call. A second attempt usually fixes the obvious tells. By the third attempt, the LLM starts introducing different tells. By the fourth attempt you are inventing slop that was not there before. Worst, you have spent four times the latency budget for diminishing returns.\"}]\n47:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-22\",{\"children\":\"We cap our regenerations at one retry. This repair directive is the key:\"}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"48:[\"$\",\"pre\",\"pre-4\",{\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L74\",\"code-0\",{\"language\":\"ts\",\"children\":\"export function buildRepairDirective(report: ValidationReport): string {\\n  const offenders = [...new Set(report.violations.map(v =\u003e v.term))]\\n    .slice(0, 25)\\n    .map(t =\u003e `  - ${t}`)\\n    .join('\\\\n');\\n\\n  return `## REPAIR DIRECTIVE\\nYour previous output failed the banned-lexicon check. The following exact\\nterms or patterns appeared and must be removed:\\n\\n${offenders}\\n\\nDo NOT paraphrase the rejected output. Re-read the source material and\\nwrite a fresh draft from scratch. Paraphrasing keeps the underlying\\ncadence and structural tells. Rewriting from source breaks them.`;\\n}\"}]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"49:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-23\",{\"children\":\"The \\\"do not paraphrase, rewrite from source\\\" instruction is the most useful line in the whole pipeline. Paraphrase prompts cause the model to keep the same paragraph skeleton and only swap synonyms — which keeps every cadence tell intact. Forcing a rewrite from source forces a different sentence-shape distribution.\"}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"4a:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-24\",{\"children\":[\"After the retry, the validator runs again. We keep whichever response has the lower slop score, even if neither is fully clean. The user always gets the best of two attempts, plus a \",[\"$\",\"code\",\"code-0\",{\"className\":\"$undefined\",\"node\":{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"code\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"lexiconWarnings\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":176,\"column\":183,\"offset\":10814},\"end\":{\"line\":176,\"column\":200,\"offset\":10831}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":176,\"column\":183,\"offset\":10814},\"end\":{\"line\":176,\"column\":200,\"offset\":10831}}},\"children\":\"lexiconWarnings\"}],\" payload so the UI can surface a small \\\"regenerate?\\\" badge if anything still slipped through.\"]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"4b:[\"$\",\"h2\",\"h2-6\",{\"id\":\"how-much-does-postgeneration-validation-slow-things-down\",\"className\":\"scroll-mt-24\",\"node\":{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"h2\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"How much does post-generation validation slow things down?\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":178,\"column\":4,\"offset\":10929},\"end\":{\"line\":178,\"column\":62,\"offset\":10987}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":178,\"column\":1,\"offset\":10926},\"end\":{\"line\":178,\"column\":62,\"offset\":10987}}},\"children\":\"How much does post-generation validation slow things down?\"}]\n4c:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-25\",{\"children\":\"Here are the numbers from our first 48 hours of telemetry, captured via PostHog:\"}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"4d:[\"$\",\"table\",\"table-0\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"thead\",\"thead-0\",{\"children\":[\"$\",\"tr\",\"tr-0\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"th\",\"th-0\",{\"children\":\"Scenario\"}],[\"$\",\"th\",\"th-1\",{\"children\":\"Frequency\"}],[\"$\",\"th\",\"th-2\",{\"children\":\"Extra latency\"}]]}]}],[\"$\",\"tbody\",\"tbody-0\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"tr\",\"tr-0\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"td\",\"td-0\",{\"children\":\"Validator scan, draft is clean\"}],[\"$\",\"td\",\"td-1\",{\"children\":\"~88%\"}],[\"$\",\"td\",\"td-2\",{\"children\":\"\u003c 5 ms\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"tr\",\"tr-1\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"td\",\"td-0\",{\"children\":\"Validator scan, retry triggered, succeeds\"}],[\"$\",\"td\",\"td-1\",{\"children\":\"~10%\"}],[\"$\",\"td\",\"td-2\",{\"children\":\"+ 1 LLM call (3–8 s social, 15–40 s long-form)\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"tr\",\"tr-2\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"td\",\"td-0\",{\"children\":\"Validator scan, retry fails to clean\"}],[\"$\",\"td\",\"td-1\",{\"children\":\"~2%\"}],[\"$\",\"td\",\"td-2\",{\"children\":\"+ 1 LLM call, ship cleaner of two\"}]]}]]}]]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"4e:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-26\",{\"children\":[\"Worst case is roughly \",[\"$\",\"strong\",\"strong-0\",{\"children\":\"2× generation time\"}],\". Not 4×, not 5×. The validator scan itself is regex over a few KB of text, sub-5ms even on a 2,000-word article.\"]}]\n4f:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-27\",{\"children\":\"We picked a single retry deliberately:\"}]\n50:[\"$\",\"ul\",\"ul-0\",{\"children\":[\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"li\",\"li-0\",{\"children\":\"LLM regression-to-the-mean makes additional retries unreliable\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"li\",\"li-1\",{\"children\":\"Long-form is already 15–40 seconds; users abandon at 2 minutes\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"li\",\"li-2\",{\"children\":\"Every retry is a billable Gemini call\"}],\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"li\",\"li-3\",{\"children\":\"Bounded retries make worst-case latency predictable for loading states\"}],\"\\n\"]}]\n51:[\"$\",\"h2\",\"h2-7\",{\"id\":\"why-we-tell-users-about-the-delay\",\"className\":\"scroll-mt-24\",\"node\":{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"h2\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"Why we tell users about the delay\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":197,\"column\":4,\"offset\":11977},\"end\":{\"line\":197,\"column\":37,\"offset\":12010}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":197,\"column\":1,\"offset\":11974},\"end\":{\"line\":197,\"column\":37,\"offset\":12010}}},\"children\":\"Why we tell users about the delay\"}]\n52:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-28\",{\"children\":\"Our product reviewer asked whether we should hide the latency to make the product feel faster. We came to the conclusion that hiding it would make the wait feel arbitrary. Surfacing it makes the wait feel earned.\"}]\n53:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-29\",{\"children\":\"The pre-generation tip on the long-form page now reads:\"}]\n54:[\"$\",\"blockquote\",\"blockquote-0\",{\"children\":[\"\\n\",[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-0\",{\"children\":[\"$\",\"em\",\"em-0\",{\"children\":\"Every draft runs through the slop validator. If AI tells slip through, we regenerate once before showing it to you.\"}]}],\"\\n\"]}]\n55:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-30\",{\"children\":[\"The mid-generation loader cycles through honest steps: \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"em-0\",{\"children\":\"Running the slop filter… Scanning for AI tells… Re-running if any slop slipped through…\"}]]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"56:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-31\",{\"children\":[\"This is the same principle we explored in \",[\"$\",\"a\",\"a-0\",{\"href\":\"https://blog.ozigi.app/how-to-make-your-linkedin-content-standout-in-2026\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"node\":{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"a\",\"properties\":{\"href\":\"https://blog.ozigi.app/how-to-make-your-linkedin-content-standout-in-2026\"},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"our LinkedIn post 2026 piece\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":207,\"column\":44,\"offset\":12593},\"end\":{\"line\":207,\"column\":72,\"offset\":12621}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":207,\"column\":43,\"offset\":12592},\"end\":{\"line\":207,\"column\":148,\"offset\":12697}}},\"children\":\"our LinkedIn post 2026 piece\"}],\",  when you charge a price (in money or time), name what the user is buying. Otherwise the price feels like a tax.\"]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"57:[\"$\",\"h2\",\"h2-8\",{\"id\":\"should-you-use-a-humanizer-api-for-your-content-instead\",\"className\":\"scroll-mt-24\",\"node\":{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"h2\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"Should you use a humanizer API For your content instead?\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":209,\"column\":4,\"offset\":12816},\"end\":{\"line\":209,\"column\":60,\"offset\":12872}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":209,\"column\":1,\"offset\":12813},\"end\":{\"line\":209,\"column\":60,\"offset\":12872}}},\"children\":\"Should you use a humanizer API For your content instead?\"}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"58:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-32\",{\"children\":[\"Someone on the team suggested the alternative path: pipe every LLM output through a third-party humanizer API, then run a \\\"tuning\\\" pass on the humanized output to recover any meaning lost in humanization. So the chain becomes \",[\"$\",\"code\",\"code-0\",{\"className\":\"$undefined\",\"node\":{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"code\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"LLM → humanizer → re-tune → ship\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":211,\"column\":227,\"offset\":13100},\"end\":{\"line\":211,\"column\":261,\"offset\":13134}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":211,\"column\":227,\"offset\":13100},\"end\":{\"line\":211,\"column\":261,\"offset\":13134}}},\"children\":\"LLM → humanizer → re-tune → ship\"}],\".\"]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"59:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-33\",{\"children\":\"The short answer is no, with one caveat. Here is the longer answer.\"}]\n5a:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-34\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",\"strong-0\",{\"children\":\"Cost stack.\"}],\" A humanizer call adds at least one round trip, often two (the rewrite + the meaning-recovery pass). For long-form, that is +5–15 seconds on top of an already long generation. For social, it can double the entire request. The validator we shipped pays this cost only on the ~12% of drafts that need it. A humanizer pays the cost on 100%.\"]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"5b:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-35\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",\"strong-0\",{\"children\":\"Detection arms race.\"}],\" Humanizer APIs are trained to fool AI-detector models like GPTZero or \",[\"$\",\"a\",\"a-0\",{\"href\":\"https://originality.ai/\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"node\":{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"a\",\"properties\":{\"href\":\"https://originality.ai/\"},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"Originality.AI\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":217,\"column\":97,\"offset\":13656},\"end\":{\"line\":217,\"column\":111,\"offset\":13670}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":217,\"column\":96,\"offset\":13655},\"end\":{\"line\":217,\"column\":137,\"offset\":13696}}},\"children\":\"Originality.AI\"}],\". That is a different goal from sounding like a person. Many humanizers degrade prose to win the detector benchmark. They introduce typos, fragmented sentences, and odd punctuation patterns that score \\\"human\\\" on a classifier but read worse to a real reader. \",[\"$\",\"a\",\"a-1\",{\"href\":\"https://www.pangram.com/\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"node\":{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"a\",\"properties\":{\"href\":\"https://www.pangram.com/\"},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"Pangram's research on detector bypass\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":217,\"column\":396,\"offset\":13955},\"end\":{\"line\":217,\"column\":433,\"offset\":13992}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":217,\"column\":395,\"offset\":13954},\"end\":{\"line\":217,\"column\":460,\"offset\":14019}}},\"children\":\"Pangram's research on detector bypass\"}],\" is the right place to start if you want the academic version.\"]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"5c:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-36\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",\"strong-0\",{\"children\":\"Meaning loss.\"}],\" The \\\"tuning\\\" pass exists in the proposed chain because humanizers regularly invert sentences, drop technical specificity, or mistranslate domain jargon. A re-tune pass on top of that adds a third LLM call where the model is now reasoning about an already-mangled draft. Each round trip introduces noise. By round three, you are far from the source material.\"]}]\n5d:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-37\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",\"strong-0\",{\"children\":\"Ownership.\"}],\" A humanizer is a black box. Our banned lexicon is a TypeScript file. When a user complains about the word \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"em-0\",{\"children\":\"delve\"}],\", we add it to the array, the dev-mode drift guard catches the prose-vs-code mismatch, and the next generation is fixed. With a humanizer, every fix is an outside vendor's roadmap.\"]}]\n5e:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-38\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",\"strong-0\",{\"children\":\"The caveat.\"}],\" A small humanizer pass \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"em-0\",{\"children\":\"can\"}],\" help in one specific scenario: when you do not control the prompt. If you are wrapping a black-box API or showing third-party AI output, you have no banned-lexicon hook into the model's instruction. In that case, a constrained humanizer (one tuned for paraphrase quality, not detector bypass) is a reasonable last resort. If you control the prompt, controlling the prompt is always cheaper, faster, and more honest.\"]}]\n5f:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-39\",{\"children\":\"For Ozigi specifically, we give the model the rules and verify the rules were followed. That is the contract our users understand.\"}]\n60:[\"$\",\"h2\",\"h2-9\",{\"id\":\"how-we-keep-the-lexicon-updated\",\"className\":\"scroll-mt-24\",\"node\":{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"h2\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"How we keep the lexicon updated\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":227,\"column\":4,\"offset\":15367},\"end\":{\"line\":227,\"column\":35,\"offset\":15398}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":227,\"column\":1,\"offset\":15364},\"end\":{\"line\":227,\"column\":35,\"offset\":15398}}},\"children\":\""])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"How we keep the lexicon updated\"}]\n61:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-40\",{\"children\":\"Two feedback loops keep the lexicon current:\"}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"62:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-41\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",\"strong-0\",{\"children\":\"Drift guard.\"}],\" The dev-mode block at the bottom of \",[\"$\",\"code\",\"code-0\",{\"className\":\"$undefined\",\"node\":{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"code\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"anti-ai.ts\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":231,\"column\":54,\"offset\":15499},\"end\":{\"line\":231,\"column\":66,\"offset\":15511}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":231,\"column\":54,\"offset\":15499},\"end\":{\"line\":231,\"column\":66,\"offset\":15511}}},\"children\":\"anti-ai.ts\"}],\" walks every entry in the structured arrays and verifies it appears in the prose rulebook. If a developer adds \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"em-0\",{\"children\":\"paradigm\"}],\" to \",[\"$\",\"code\",\"code-1\",{\"className\":\"$undefined\",\"node\":{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"code\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"BANNED_WORDS\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":231,\"column\":191,\"offset\":15636},\"end\":{\"line\":231,\"column\":205,\"offset\":15650}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":231,\"column\":191,\"offset\":15636},\"end\":{\"line\":231,\"column\":205,\"offset\":15650}}},\"children\":\"BANNED_WORDS\"}],\" but forgets to add it to the §1A list in the prose, the dev console warns on next reload. CI promotes the warning to an error.\"]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"63:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-42\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"strong\",\"strong-0\",{\"children\":\"Telemetry.\"}],\" Every generation logs three properties to PostHog: \",[\"$\",\"code\",\"code-0\",{\"className\":\"$undefined\",\"node\":{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"code\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"lexiconViolations\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":233,\"column\":67,\"offset\":15845},\"end\":{\"line\":233,\"column\":86,\"offset\":15864}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":233,\"column\":67,\"offset\":15845},\"end\":{\"line\":233,\"column\":86,\"offset\":15864}}},\"children\":\"lexiconViolations\"}],\", \",[\"$\",\"code\",\"code-1\",{\"className\":\"$undefined\",\"node\":{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"code\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"lexiconSlopScore\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":233,\"column\":88,\"offset\":15866},\"end\":{\"line\":233,\"column\":106,\"offset\":15884}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":233,\"column\":88,\"offset\":15866},\"end\":{\"line\":233,\"column\":106,\"offset\":15884}}},\"children\":\"lexiconSlopScore\"}],\", \",[\"$\",\"code\",\"code-2\",{\"className\":\"$undefined\",\"node\":{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"code\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"lexiconRetried\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":233,\"column\":108,\"offset\":15886},\"end\":{\"line\":233,\"column\":124,\"offset\":15902}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":233,\"column\":108,\"offset\":15886},\"end\":{\"line\":233,\"column\":124,\"offset\":15902}}},\"children\":\"lexiconRetried\"}],\". We chart these weekly. When a new term starts trending in the violation feed (Gemini picked up \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"em-0\",{\"children\":\"crucial\"}],\" in week two — caught it in 31 generations before adding to the list), we promote it.\"]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"64:[\"$\",\"p\",\"p-43\",{\"children\":[\"The result is a lexicon that grows from real production data instead of guesswork. We have written before about why production telemetry beats theoretical evals in \",[\"$\",\"a\",\"a-0\",{\"href\":\"https://blog.ozigi.app/rag-architecture-for-enterprise-data\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\